nodes.bodyText:
I ran a test locally on a project and it works perfectly!
I do have one final suggestion. context here is loaded only once, so using a lock every time we acquire seems heavy handed. What do you think about using a double checked lock? We would have to change context to be volatile on line 51
private volatile Context context;

And then rewrite this method
    private Context getContext() {
        Context ctx = this.context;
        if (ctx == null) {
            synchronized (this) {
                ctx = this.context;
                if (ctx == null) {
                    this.context = ctx = vertx.getOrCreateContext();
                }
            }
        }
        return ctx;
    }

We could do the same with the latest strategy - maybe even abstract it to reduce duplicate code.
Theoretically we would see a 100x performance gain.

